  "root_text": {
    "iti59:0.1": "Itivuttaka 59 ",
    "iti59:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti59:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti59:0.4": "Māradheyyasutta ",
    "iti59:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti59:2.1": "“Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu atikkamma māradheyyaṁ ādiccova virocati. ",
    "iti59:2.2": "Katamehi tīhi? ",
    "iti59:2.3": "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asekhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekhena samādhikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti—",
    "iti59:2.4": "imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu atikkamma māradheyyaṁ ādiccova virocatī”ti. ",
    "iti59:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti59:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti59:3.1": "“Sīlaṁ samādhi paññā ca, ",
    "iti59:3.2": "yassa ete subhāvitā; ",
    "iti59:3.3": "Atikkamma māradheyyaṁ, ",
    "iti59:3.4": "ādiccova virocatī”ti. ",
    "iti59:4.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti59:4.2": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "iti59:4.3": "Paṭhamo vaggo. ",
    "iti59:5.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "iti59:5.1": "Mūladhātu atha vedanā duve, ",
    "iti59:5.2": "Esanā ca duve āsavā duve; ",
    "iti59:5.3": "Taṇhāto ca atha māradheyyato, ",
    "iti59:5.4": "Vaggamāhu paṭhamanti muttamanti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti59:0.1": "So It Was Said 59 ",
    "iti59:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti59:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti59:0.4": "Māra’s Dominion ",
    "iti59:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti59:2.1": "“Mendicants, a mendicant with these three qualities has slipped free of Māra’s dominion and shines like the sun. ",
    "iti59:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti59:2.3": "It’s when they have the entire spectrum of the adept’s ethics, immersion, and wisdom. ",
    "iti59:2.4": "A mendicant with these three qualities has slipped free of Māra’s dominion and shines like the sun.” ",
    "iti59:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti59:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti59:3.1": "“Whoever has well developed ",
    "iti59:3.2": "ethics, immersion, and wisdom ",
    "iti59:3.3": "has slipped free of Māra’s dominion ",
    "iti59:3.4": "and shines like the sun.” ",
    "iti59:4.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti59:5.3": "Taṇhāto ca atha → taṇhāto atha (sya-all) "
  },
